== Rice ==

Wash and dry produce. Open and drain @tofu{1%unit}; press out excess water with #paper towels{}. Halve crosswise, then stand tofu upright and halve vertically. Lay flat and cut into ¾-inch cubes.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Fresh Salsa ==

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @tomato{1}(finely diced), @red onion{1}(finely chopped, 2 TBSP), half the @lime{1}(zested and quartered) zest, a squeeze of lime juice, a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, and as much @jalapeño{1}(halved, deseeded, and finely chopped) as you like.

Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

> Leave jalapeño seeds in for more spice!

== Beef ==

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion slices and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add beef, @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and finely chopped), @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and another big pinch of @salt{pinch}.

> If you like things spicy, add any remaining jalapeño.

Using a #spatula{}, arrange beef into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up into pieces; cook, stirring occasionally, until beef is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Swap in tofu or chicken for beef (no need to break up into pieces!).

== Broth ==

To pan with beef, stir in @tomato paste{1%unit} and @beef stock concentrate{1%unit}, then add ¼ cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted; turn off heat.

== Lime Crema ==

While beef cooks, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining lime zest and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with beef mixture, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, salsa, and crema.

Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} and remaining lime wedges on the side.